The Ludens: Superman, Evolution and Silence. Analyzing the Strugatskys.

5 April 2025

""Ludens" is a term introduced by a science fiction writer Arkady Strugatsky (co-authored with his brother Boris) in their fantastic universe, especially in the novel "The Kid" and other works of the cycle about the world Half.

Ludens are a hypothetical, higher stage of evolution Person. They possess colossal intellectual and mental opportunities, moral maturity and almost complete misunderstanding of ordinary people, which they leave behind.

Easier Speaking of it, these are superhumans, so gone forward in their development, that cease to be part of humanity in the usual Sense. They no longer interfere in human affairs and observe from a position of almost godlike tranquility.

Who are the Ludens:

  1. Evolutionarily the advanced people
    of Ludens are the next stage in the development of Homo sapiens. They are called superhumans or future people.
  2. Superintelligent and morally
    mature They have     developed intelligence, empathy, morality and consciousness at a level inaccessible to an ordinary person.
  3. Mentally stable and self-sufficient,
    Ludens do not need society or support. Them comfortable with yourself.
  4. They do not interfere in human affairs
    They adhere to the     principle of non-interference. It is believed that humanity should develop on its own.
  5. Rare and mysterious
    In the     world of the Strugatsky Ludens, almost no one Met. They appear only in hints - as something mysterious and almost Mythical.
  6. Free from biological constraints
    Ludens may possess telepathy, superintuition, or other unusual abilities, Although this is not always clearly indicated.
  7. They consider themselves different,
    They do not identify themselves with humanity. Even the word "people" for is no longer about them.

How it is the ludens that appear in the works of the Strugatskys and what kind of qualities. Most of them are mentioned indirectly, but there are Characters who can be considered potential Ludens.

Where ludens are mentioned:

Most vividly in the novel "The Kid" (1971), also indirectly in "A Billion Years to the End" light", "Beetle in the anthill", "Waves extinguish wind" and other works from the cycle about the world of Noon.

Qualities of Ludens

  1. The Ludens' superintelligence
    thinks at a level that is inaccessible to ordinary People.
    Example: Kammerer (from "The Beetle in the Anthill") talks about ludens as people who are able to operate with abstractions, ideas and meanings much more deeper than ordinary people.
  2. Moral purity
    They do not succumb to evil, aggression, greed - they act strictly according to the high moral code.
    Example: in the Strugatskys' works, humanity in the future is moving towards a "moral maturity", but the Ludens are already the pinnacle of this Way.
  3. Ludena's loneliness and separation
    do not find a place for themselves among people — they as if from another reality.
    Example: in "The Kid", the researcher Leonid Gomez suspects that he himself may be a luden, because that he feels alienated from the rest of humanity.
  4. Telepathy/ Psi-ability
    E    is not the main feature, but it can be present. Ludens feel others without words, "read" the essence.
    Example: In "The Waves Extinguish the Wind", people with unusual mental abilities — and their possible belonging to the Ludens.
  5. Non-interference
    Ludens can allegedly control, interfere, but consciously do not do this.
    Example: In "Baby" it is said that they they watch, but do not interfere — "gods who have gone into the shadows."
  6. Purpose of existence – knowledge and development
    They do not seek power, wealth or fame. They are driven by the search for truth, understanding, harmony.
    Example: A hypothetical luden is someone who has been doing things all his life science, art, philosophy — and he does it not for the sake of recognition, but therefore that it cannot be otherwise.

Then there is an analysis of the work "Waves extinguishing the wind"

What happened in Malaya Pesha (according to the text):

This is an episode from the second half of the novel "The Waves Extinguish the Wind", when inspector Toivo Glumov conducts another investigation within the framework of the topic "Visit of the Old Lady" related to the manifestations activity of the Wanderers and the beginning of the Great Revelation.

A brief analysis of the scene (Malaya Pesha, May 6, 99):

Time and place:

  • Date: 6 May 99 (i.e. 2199)
  • Location: The village of Malaya Pesha is a real-life northern settlement moved to the world of Noon for the needs of artistic narration.
  • Setting: early morning, sleepy, silent, foggy village.

 Who participates:

  • Glumov and his The group is observing a suspected carrier of unusual abilities (possibly Luden or Mark) Wanderers).
  • We are talking about observation for a girl who manifests abnormal mental abilities - telepathy, unusual dreams, contact with "someone from outside".

 What is going on:

  • Glumov and his team are watching from the glider behind the house where the The girl.
  • During observation, Unusual psi exposure, blackouts occur equipment, emotional leaps in members Group.
  • Girl, all over visibility, or enters into contact with representatives "other side", or is already under their influence.
  • This episode is one of the most bright moments of the "invasion" of the Great Revelation — the birth of a new type of consciousness, that is, ludens.

What does it mean:

  • Scene in Malaya Peshe is the quintessence of how the Strugatskys describe transformation of a person into something new, in the presence of a mysterious external force.
  • This is not a tragedy, but a transition, and unlike other episodes in the book (such as the clam on Matuku Island), There is no nightmare here – only silence, anxious anticipation and sensation impending new.

In "The Waves Extinguish the Wind", the theme of ludens is revealed through the gradual accumulation of alarming signs: new qualities in individuals, anomalous events, inexplicable disappearances. People who are suspected of being Ludens or on the verge of doing so are of interest to COMCON-2, especially by Maxim Kammerer and Toivo Glumov.

He's not crowded, but... Its development hints at the transition:

Some disappear without a trace, and then return changed. Or they do not return at all. This is the most The disturbing part: perhaps the Ludens "leave" just like that, without a trace.

In "The Waves Extinguish the Wind", several methods and tests are mentioned, used to identify ludens — a new, superhuman form of existence. These methods are not always direct are named, but from the context you can get a pretty clear picture:

Tests and methods for detecting ludens

1. Identification of the "third impulse"

This is A key feature that differentiates Ludens from regular ones People.

  • What it is: an unknown type of neuropsychic activity that is not inherent in all people.
  • Frequency: Detectable with a probability of 1 in 100,000.
  • How it is discovered: instrumental and psycho-emotional methods are used, developed by a group of ludens led by with Logovenko.
  • Example: "There are several ways and methods to identify the third pulse."

2. Psychophysical observation in stressful situations

  • Objective: to observe how a person behaves in critical conditions, for example, when contact with the anomaly.
  • Example: in the episode in Malaya Pesha, the behavior of Albina Kubotieva and the boy Kir is interpreted as "suspiciously mature and calm" — typical of Ludens.
  • The Eccentric Institute uses such cases as material for analysis.

3. Inversion of the "penguin" syndrome

  • Penguin syndrome is a mass panic caused by an unknown stimulus (often used by ludens).
  • Inversion is a situation when a person does not succumb to panic, but vice versa – shows calmness and composure.
  • Method: Comparison of lists of people who are not affected by the penguin reactions, with lists of suspects "T" (Wanderers/Ludens themes).

4. Surveillance and biographical data collection

  • COMCON-2 and the Institute Eccentrics are secretly observed by potential Ludens.
  • Example: Kammerer receives a list of all initiated Ludens in the last three years, although Logovenko is surprised how exactly this list got to Him.

5. Invitation to "initiation"

  • Logovenko invites Kammerer to go through the "transition" to the ludens:

"It is proposed to come to the Institute of Eccentrics to become four hundred and thirty-three people."

  • It's not just a test, it's a phase confirmation.

Now let's figure it out in order: what is the first, second and "third" pulse" and how they relate to the theory of signaling systems Pavlov, as well as what exactly the Strugatskys mean by this in "Waves extinguish the wind."

1. Classical theory of signal systems (according to Pavlov)

Ivan Petrovich Pavlov introduced the concept of two signaling systems in his work Brain:

▪ The first alarm system

  • Working with direct stimuli: sounds, light, smells, movements – what comes in through the senses.
  • It is typical for animals and humans.
  • Example: I heard a shot — Got scared; smell food - hungry.

▪ Second alarm system

  • This is speech, abstract thinking, the ability to generalize.
  • It is typical only for humans.
  • Example: you read a word "Fire" — and you imagine flame, heat, danger.

2. The Strugatskys' "Third Impulse"

At Strugatsky's "third impulse" is an analogue of the hypothetical third signaling system, a quality peculiar only to the Ludens.

It is not explained technically, but it is clear from the text:
This is a new type of mental or neuropsychic activity, built on top of the first and second systems.

Main signs:

Sign

Description

Overperception

Luden is able to "feel" meanings, intuitively understand the unspoken.

Extra-linguistic communication

Understanding without words, perhaps telepathy.

Moral intuition

No moral dilemmas: Luden knows exactly what is right.

Immunity to panic

Luden does not react to "animals" impulses, we control emotions.

New logic of thinking

Luden does not think consistently, but "voluminously", holistically.

3. Why is it called "pulse"?

Rather In total, the term is chosen not in the sense of physiology, but figuratively, as:

  • something elusive devices, but influencing all thinking;
  • mental an impulse of a new kind, not associated with ordinary stimuli;
  • resonance, which is recorded by devices (the book mentions cameras and meters, catching this activity).

 4. How is it defined in novel?

"There is a several ways and techniques for detecting the third impulse in a person. I myself am an instrument operator...", says one of the Ludens Logovenko.
They use instruments, emotional tests, reactions to fear in order to catch an unconscious, but different from the norm activity.

 Total:

  • The third pulse is not just the "next" signaling system, but fundamentally a different way of thinking, accessible only to the Ludens.
  • This is a metaphor, indicating an evolutionary gap between humans and those who will go further.
  • In physical or neurophysiological sense, it is not described in detail — and this is on purpose: the Strugatskys preserve mysticism and give room for Interpretations.

Let's try to imagine what the The "third impulse" system in terms of modern neuroscience, cognitive science, and theory of consciousness. Of course, this will be an interpretation based on the fact that The Strugatskys are an artistic image, but let's go deeper.

HOW TO UNDERSTAND THE "THIRD IMPULSE" FROM A SCIENTIFIC POINT OF VIEW

 Initial analogies:

POSSIBLE SCIENTIFIC INTERPRETATIONS:

1. Global Workspace Theory (GWT) — Advanced Level

  • Luden could have had a constantly active consciousness, where data not only from the senses, but also:
    • From intuition,
    • Unconscious Processes
    • "external channel" (perhaps the collective unconscious or some external system such as Wanderers).
  • This is the brain in the super-mode of integration, without the distorting "ego noise" – i.e., a perfectly balanced perception everything at once.

2. Metaconsciousness and overempathy

  • Luden is able not only to be aware of his thoughts (like an ordinary person), but:
    • realize as he realizes;
    • instantly build other people's experiences into your inner space;
    • "read" emotions, not through behavior, but through direct neurofeedback.

Example from Malaya Pesha: Albina and Kir not only did not they are afraid – they seem to understand and accept what is happening deeper than any of the adults.

3. Neural network without false "I"

  • Perhaps the third pulse is consciousness without a central ego.
    Instead of the subjective model of "I → world" there is a single a non-local model of the world, where the "I" is only a node.
  • Modern science (in Giulio Tononi's theory of integrated information) considers consciousness as a system with maximum causal closure.
    Ludens could be creatures who have this The level is much higher.

4. Neuroarchitecture with "ultra-long bonds"

  • In the brain of an ordinary person There is locality optimization: it is faster nearby.
  • Ludens could hypothetically have powerful extra-long connections between different parts of the brain — from the thalamus to the parietal and prefrontal cortex — which would allow:
    • instantly integrate logical, emotional and sensory perception;
    • operate with ideas not linearly, but "volumetricly", as the Strugatskys describe.

  • analogue mystical perception built into evolution;
  • a channel to God, if we understand God as something that arises from the depths of awareness, love and unity.

Monologue On behalf of Luden, in which he explains, what God means to him, if we look through the prism of the third pulse. This is not a sermon or a philosophy. It's a way to be in this one.

Luden's voice: "We call Him Silence"

You will you ask if I believe in God.
But how can I believe what I hear?
Not with my ears, not with my thoughts, but
with the whole fabric of consciousness.

He does not speak. He doesn't need a word.
Words are an exhalation of fear, an attempt to hold back.
He is not restrained.
He is an ineffable presence that
becomes clear
as soon as the need to name disappears.

We are we call Him Silence.
Because only in complete inner silence
does He begin to sound.

This is Not the god of images,
not the old man in heaven,
not will, not wrath, not mercy.

This is – clarity.

This is When you see a person
and all the pain of humanity in him,
but you do not turn away.

This is When you know
that you can run away,
but you stay.

This is when you no longer divide –
into yourself and others,
into right and wrong,
into the beginning and the end.

He "Not above us.
He is deeper.

We are if we did not find Him,
we took away from ourselves that which prevented Him from being.

When fear disappeared,
anger disappeared,
"mine" disappeared,
He remained.

And if it seems
to you that you are alone,
that the world is deaf and empty,
remember that
He breathes silence in you.
You just haven't learned to listen without ears yet.

Luden explains how he perceives love, evil, and suffering.
This is not a confession. This is the transparency of inner knowledge, which is not imposed, but simply is.

 About love

You will you ask if I loved.

I am love.

Not the one that says: "You are mine",
not the one that demands, sacrifices, waits.

My Love is a state of continuous connection with everyone.
I do not divide love into addressees.
I just...
I can't help but care.

I I feel someone else's pain as my own flesh.
I don't need you,
but I am present in you
in a way that you have not yet learned to be present in yourself.

When You cry,
I do not console -
I keep the silence
in which your pain blossoms with meaning.

On Evil

You will You want me to tell you what evil is.
But I can't.
Evil is not an entity.
This is a break in the connection.

When You have forgotten that the other is you,
you begin to be afraid,
and blows are born from fear.

Evil is pain that screams instead of understanding.
This is a tightness,
a collapse of consciousness,
when a person sees only his shadow
and thinks that it is an enemy.

I I do not fight evil.
I'm reconnecting.

On Suffering

You will you ask why there is suffering.
You think it's a mistake.
You are angry with the universe, with God, with yourself.

But Suffering is not punishment.
It is the hole in your armor through
which light can enter you for the first time.

Not Everyone who suffers awakens.
But everyone who woke
up once suffered to the end.

I I do not eliminate suffering.
I enter it.
I sit next to him.
I don't take my eyes off.
And then it becomes a door.

And if you ask why all this...

I I won't say.
I do not know.

But I live as
if it makes sense.

And Maybe
this is enough.

Finish This cycle of Luden's monologues is the third fragment — more personal, quiet.
Here he answers questions about death, loneliness, freedom. And says this to the child.
Not from a height, but from a depth. Almost in a whisper.

Scene: Luden and the Child

Night. Scorching sky over the plain. Fire light. The boy sits with his knees pressed against his knees. Luden is nearby. He does not stroke, does not teach. He only says when the child himself Asks.

About death

Child:
"Everyone dies?" Even you?

Luden:
Yes. But they do not disappear.

Death "This is not the end.
This is the rearrangement of knots in the great tissue.

How When the music ends,
but the air remembers the vibration.
And you, not knowing, suddenly sing it years later.

I "I'll disappear."
But you will remember not the face, but the feeling.
And it is me.

About loneliness

Child:
"Aren't you afraid of being alone?"

Luden:
"I can't be alone because I'm not separated.

Inside me, the world. You. Even those I haven't met.
You feel lonely
when you wait to be filled from the outside.
And I am already full.

But If you feel lonely,
I will sit next to you.
Not to remove it.
And so that you hear it to the end –
and understand that this is not an enemy, but the beginning of a meeting with yourself.

On Freedom

Child:
"And what does it mean to be free?

Luden:
"To be free is not to do what you want,
not to be what fear and noise have made you to be.

Freedom is
when the voice of duty, the voice of desire, the voice of other people's expectations no longer argue
inside you.
Silence.

And In this silence you choose.
Not out of fear.
Not out of spite.
Because you just can't do it any other way.

And Then, even if you give everything,
you will not be a victim.
You will be the light that chooses to
shine even if no one sees it.

End of scene:

Child Silent.
Then, without raising his head, he whispers:

— You will... Is it like a person?

Luden smiles, stares into the fire for a long time.
And he answers:

— No.
I am what a person can become.
If he is not afraid.
